          "30078:<PUBKEY>:tides-end-09-recipes:item:rope"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "Weathered planks creak beneath your feet as the dock juts out over grey-green water. Fishing boats knock gently against their moorings, their paint flaking in long pale strips. The smell of salt and tar hangs in the still air.\n\nA coil of **rope** lies near a bollard, forgotten by some fisherman.\n\nA sandy path follows the shoreline east toward the beach, and a cobbled road leads north to the village square."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "tides-end-09-recipes:place:the-beach"
        ],
        [
          "t",
